history.content: Please check your email. The communications from the college state that the APR is not reliable for major requirements. It should only be used for university and L&S college requirements.

I have completed my 2 upper devision tech elective according to my CS advisor (I've taken Stat 133 and POLSCI C135)

but in the new tool released in cal central (Academic Progress Report), POLSCI C135 (Game theory) isn't included towards the tech elective requirement and it appears as "not satisfied"

should I be worried about this?
history.subject: elective requirements not satisfied according to new tool
